# Cloudflare Pages natively serves /page and /page.html with the same content,
# but this does NOT make them SEO-equivalent: both return 200, so Google can
# crawl and index both independently. Explicit 301s (below) are what actually
# consolidate ranking signals onto a single canonical URL.

# guides/index.astro builds to /guides.html (build.format: 'file' in astro.config.mjs
# outputs foo/index.astro as foo.html, not a foo/ directory). /guides/ was never a
# real path - the two rules that used to live here (/guides -> /guides/ and
# /guides.html -> /guides/) redirected working URLs to a 404. Fixed: redirect the
# non-existent /guides/ to the real page instead.
/guides/ /guides.html 301
/guides /guides.html 301

# Deprecated age/height-specific template pages, consolidated into hub pages.
# These used to be handled via robots.txt Disallow + canonical tag, but that
# combo doesn't work: Google can't read a canonical tag on a page it's blocked
# from crawling in the first place. Redirecting properly passes link equity to
# the hub pages instead of leaving these stuck in a blocked/orphaned state.
